PATH & Parent-Child Functions (DAX) – Brief Note
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
What is PATH?
PATH(Child, Parent) shows the hierarchy path from top parent to child.
Returns a text string like "1|2|4|5" (IDs separated by |).

Key Functions
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
PATH() → Full chain of IDs (lineage).
Example: CEO → VP → Manager → Staff → "1|2|4|5".
PATHLENGTH() → How many levels.
Example: "1|2|4|5" → 4 levels.

PATHITEM() → Pick a specific level from PATH.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
Example: PATHITEM("1|2|4|5", 2) → 2 (VP).

PATHITEMREVERSE() → Pick from bottom.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
Example: PATHITEMREVERSE("1|2|4|5", 1) → 5 (Staff).

PATHCONTAINS() → Check if ID exists in path.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
Example: PATHCONTAINS("1|2|4|5", 2) → TRUE.

Use Cases

Org Chart: CEO → VP → Manager → Staff.
Product Categories: Category → Subcategory → Product.
Geography: Country → State → City.

Shortcut to remember:
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
PATH = lineage,
PATHLENGTH = depth,
PATHITEM = pick a level,
PATHCONTAINS = check membership.
